d dehydration of imidazole-4-glycol and possible oxidation of related alcohols, but direct hydrothermal mineral-catalyzed conversion using the proposed settings is not experimentally established in the histidine literature. This pathway reaches the target, but the key connector is speculative.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_008\",\n        \"rxn_011\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Recast rxn_011 as a speculative connector with explicit sulfur/ferric-ion rationale rather than a firm hydrothermal step.\",\n        \"Move rxn_011 to a milder surface or redox-cycling interface environment instead of hot hydrothermal conditions to better preserve imidazole intermediates.\",\n        \"Provide literature-backed oxidant choice for alcohol-to-aldehyde conversion.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.42,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.88,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.46,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.91\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.72,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.84,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.78,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.77,\n      \"feedback\": \"The alternate Shen branch via erythrose + formaldehyde + ammonia is literature-grounded, but this pathway depends on two uncertain connectors: hydrothermal generation of formaldehyde from formate and conversion of imidazole-4-ethanol/glycol to the aldehyde. The core histidine logic is coherent, yet the network overstates confidence in upstream hydrothermal formaldehyde chemistry relative to the cited histidine literature.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_002\",\n        \"rxn_011\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Treat hydrothermal for