2\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Histidine", "overall_strategy": "The network is centered on the best-supported prebiotic histidine route reported by Shen and coworkers: upstream HCN-based and sugar-forming chemistry supplies erythrose, erythrose reacts with formamidine near pH ~6 at 80 \u00b0C to give imidazole-4-acetaldehyde and imidazole-4-glycol, and imidazole-4-acetaldehyde then undergoes Strecker chemistry with NH3 and HCN to yield histidine. To satisfy systems-level connectivity while remaining literature-grounded, the network includes only one direct target-forming core and treats additional routes as convergent feeder pathways into the experimentally supported intermediates erythrose, imidazole-4-glycol, imidazole-4-acetaldehyde, HCN, and formamidine. Alternative direct histidine-forming nodes are explicitly marked speculative only where the literature itself frames them as unresolved or indirect.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", "iupac_name": "molecular hydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "CH2O2", "iupac_name": "methanoic acid", "common_name": "formic acid/formate", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O2/c2-1-3/h1H,(H,2,3)", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Hydrothermal"}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "HCN", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "CH5N", "iupac_name": "azane", "common_name": "ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": null}